You're alone man, my dad has threatened to kill me as well. I've had a similar situation to you. I'm Asian so personally I got beat a lot as a child and once my dad tried to chop my sisters hand off when she was in elementary school, it was very traumatizing and he's done many things close to that degree bordering insanity.  Idk how bad the abuse really is in your case but if I could give you any words of advice then I'd say to not fuel your dad's anger as hard as it may be. If he is that unstable it's not worth the risk. Don't lose yourself in the process and remember what you stand for but don't get hurt and stay safe.
Basketball. I was a 6'2 skinny guy.

Could you describe what it is you want? I believe I have been in your dilemma before, it was only till not too long ago that I made a break through in my social life. I've been bullied throughout most of my childhood so I became very reserved. Maybe I could give some insight.

I think this is a bit contradictory. To believe that you will be lonely forever and that you're not ok with that shows me that you've got some things to sort out, and that's ok. But until you do sort things out, I wouldn't worry about it. It's all part of the process and even if you feel like shit, keep trucking through life. You'd be surprised how many "problems" just vanish when you have confidence, forgive yourself, and start being ok failing. Best of luck.

Best of wishes.
